<Author>j34cha
<Content>I loved Clarion!!! Check-in: There was only one other person in line (we checked in around 9 at night) and the lady processed it fairly quickly. She was polite, and even offered to give me and a friend double beds instead of the original queen bed which i think was more expensive. Staff were friendly.The Elevator: The elevator was slow. There are two elevators for guests to use, but when i was there, the other one was broken so we always had to wait for the one elevator. When we were leaving, I saw somebody fixing the other one. The room: Initally when I went into the room, it stunk a little. But you kind of get use to it. Not sure if all the rooms were like this or not. We turned the AC full blast. It seemed to help. The beds were comfortable and big. Pillows were fluffy. There is no bedside clock for some reason so bring your watch or turn on the t.v. for the time. The room was pretty big! There is a sink outside besides the complimentary coffee maker. THey also provide you with glass cups and disposal cups. There is a working desk and a connection that allows you to have internet setup. They have a sofa. Not sure if it is a sofa bed or not. The bathroom was HUGE. They have the usual tub, sink etc. and lots of space and mirrors. Ice: Personally, i didn't get any ice but the ice machine was broken on the 11th floor i believe. I always saw people retrieving ice.Pool: The pool was outdoor. Didn't swim in it.Location: Clarion is next to the convention centre, and is located across the street from 2 different metromowovers (a free shuttle that transports you within miami downtown). Very convient location if you don't have a car. Within walking distance to bayside or you can take the free shuttle. Noise: Minimal to none. You might occassionally hear a metromowover, but it's nothing to complain of. Overall I would highly recommend this hotel to anybody. I gave them 4/5 stars because the elevator issue was sort of annoying but the rooms etc. were great! Great value for your money. 
